language: East Sumbanese, Umbu Ratu Nggai dialect

annotation: PAN *utaq, why?, initial q not explained

language: Kadazan Dusun of Taginambur, Kota Belud, Sabah, Malaysia

annotation: = (he) vomits; could be: ka la lua

Two forms must be reconstructed for 'to vomit' in POc and PCP: *mumuta and *lua. *mumuta continues a PMP etymon. Rotuman has a contrast between mumufa 'to vomit, spew' and  lua 'to spit or cast out of the mouth'.
